snippet.title: Jhoom Sharaabi (Song)â€“ De De Pyaar De 2 | Ajay Devgn, Rakul Preet Singh | Yo Yo Honey Singh | 14 Nov
snippet.description:
Move over couples - this wedding season belongs to the uncles! Ajay Devgn, Rakul Preet Singh & Yo Yo Honey Singh drop the craziest dance track of 2025! Jhoom Sharaabi - Song Out Now!

De De Pyaar De 2 is directed by Anshul Sharma, produced by T-Seriesâ€™ Bhushan Kumar & Krishan Kumar, and Luv Filmsâ€™ Luv Ranjan & Ankur Garg. The film is set to release in cinemas on 14th November 2025.

#JhoomSharabi #DeDePyaarDe2 

Song Credits:
Singer, Music, Rap Lyrics - Yo Yo Honey Singh 
Vocals - Athar Hayat 
Director of Choreography - Ganesh Acharya 
Additional Rhythm Programming: DJ Van
Mixed by - Vinod Verma
Mastered by - Hommie Dilliwala
Digital Promotions and Strategy - Rajdeep Mayer
Music Label - T-Series

Movie Credits:
Directed By: Anshul Sharma 
Written By: Tarun Jain & Luv Ranjan 
Produced By: Bhushan Kumar, Krishan Kumar
Produced by: Luv Ranjan & Ankur Garg
Story: Luv Ranjan 
Director of Photography: Sudhir K. Chaudhary 
Music: Hitesh Sonik 
Film Editor: Chetan M. Solanki 
Production Designer: Sumit Basu, Manini Mishra 
Costumes: Samidha Wangnoo 
Sound: Dhiman Karmakar
Creative Director: Tarun Jain
Casting Director: Vicky Sidana 
Executive Producer: Richard De Varda 
Associate Producer: Ashwinder Singh

Lyrics:

Khali bottle hai, bottle mein gin hai
Aur jinki bottle hai
Aankhein hai laal, behke hai kadam
Jin jinki bottle hai
Hothon pe hai laali, muh pe gaali
Jab khulti bottle hai
Dhakkan kholo toh isse rooh nikle
Ye hilti bottle hai
Koi kehta hai dil ko chhuti hai
Aur ghum chupati hai
Koi kehta hai ye mashooka ko
Dil se bulati hai
Koi kehta hai iske peene se
Aadat lag jaati hai
Main toh piyunga kyuki
Ye mere budget mein aati hai
Haaye

Jhoom barabar jhoom sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom
Jhoom barabar jhoom sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom
Kaali ghata hai, mast fiza hai
Kaali ghata hai, mast fiza hai
Jaam uthakar ghoom ghoom ghoom
Jhoom barabar sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom
Jhoom barabar sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom

Aaj angoor ki beti se mohabbat karle
Sheikh sahab ki nasihat se bagawat karle
Iski beti ne utha rakhi hai sar par duniya
Ye toh accha hua angoor ke beta na hua
Kum se kum soorat e saqi ka nazara karle
Aake maikhane mein jeene ka sahara karle
Aankh milte hi jawani ka mazaa aayega
Tujhko angoor ke paani ka mazaa aayega
Har nazar apni basad shauk gulaabi karde
Itni peele ke zamane ko sharaabi karde

Jaam jab saamne aaye toh mukarna kaisa
Jaam jab saamne aaye toh mukarna kaisa (chorus repeat)
Baat jab peene pe aa jaaye toh darna kaisa
Baat jab peene pe aa jaaye toh darna kaisa (chorus repeat)
Dhoom machi hai, maikhane mein
Dhoom machi hai, maikhane mein tu bhi machale
Dhoom dhoom dhoom

Jhoom barabar jhoom sharaabi, jhoom barabar jhoom
Jhoom barabar jhoom sharaabi, jhoom barabar jhoom

Raat ko maikhane mein baitha tha
Mashooka mil gayi
Hui jab shikwe shikwa phir saali
Ek bottle khul gayi
Uski aankho se jab tapka lahu
Meri rooh tak hil gayi
Parose jab maine do jaam
Uski tabiyat khil gayi
Mujhko boli ke mera aashiq hai toh
Kyu satata hai
Aashiq hai ya qatil hai mera
Jab khanjar chalata hai
Kabhi mere gharpe dera tha
Maikhane jaata hai
Maikhane jaake kis sautan ke
Bistar mein sojata hai
Haaye

Jhoom barabar jhoom sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom
Jhoom barabar jhoom sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom
Jhoom barabar jhoom sharabi, jhoom barabar jhoom


___________________________________

snippet.description:
Woh Ikkis Ka Tha, Ikkis Ka Hi Rahega! 

Dinesh Vijan and Maddock Films present #Ikkis, a true untold story of Indiaâ€™s youngest Param Vir Chakra awardee - Second Lieutenant Arun Khetarpal directed by Sriram Raghavan.

#IkkisTrailer Out Now!

Share your #QissaAtIkkis because every legendary story starts young.

In cinemas December 2025!

India vs Australia Live Match Today 
India vs Australia Live Cricket Score 
IND vs AUS Live Match Today 
Cricket Live Score 
Live Cricket Match Today

When: Australia v India, 2nd T20I, October 31, 2025, 19:15 hrs Local Time, 19:15 hrs AEDT, 13:45 hrs IST

Where: MCG, Melbourne

What to expect: After a no result game in Canberra, signs aren't the brightest in Melbourne two days later. Ironically the Victorian capital has had flawless weather over the last two days but there's already been rain in the air on Friday morning with the clouds casting a very sombre look up in the skies. Most of the radars show the rains relenting post 5 pm, which could possibly allow for the match starting on time. Like in the last few summers, there'll be intrigue around how the pitch plays at the MCG, not just for the 40 overs here but for what it could mean for the rest of the season.

Team News

Australia

Though there were some expensive overs in between rain breaks for most of the Aussie bowlers on show, there is unlikely to be any changes made from the XI that fronted up in Canberra with Josh Philippe to continue as a specialist batter.

Probable XI:Travis Head, Mitchell Marsh (c), Josh Inglis (wk), Marcus Stoinis, Tim David, Mitch Owen, Josh Philippe, Nathan Ellis, Xavier Bartlett, Matthew Kuhnemann, Josh Hazlewood

India

Not for the first time, there will be eyebrows raised over the exclusion of Arshdeep Singh, India's most successful bowler in this format, in favour of Harshit Rana who adds some batting muscle to the lower-order. But India too will in all likelihood stick to the same combination from Wednesday night.

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav (c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson (wk), Shivam Dube, Axar Patel, Harshit Rana, Kuldeep Yadav, Varun Chakravarthy, Jasprit Bumrah

Squads:
Australia Squad: Mitchell Marsh(c), Travis Head, Josh Inglis(w), Tim David, Mitchell Owen, Marcus Stoinis, Josh Philippe, Xavier Bartlett, Nathan Ellis, Matthew Kuhnemann, Josh Hazlewood, Sean Abbott, Matthew Short, Ben Dwarshuis, Tanveer Sangha
India Squad: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav(c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson(w), Shivam Dube, Axar Patel, Harshit Rana, Kuldeep Yadav, Varun Chakaravarthy, Jasprit Bumrah, Rinku Singh, Washington Sundar, Arshdeep Singh, Jitesh Sharma

When: Australia v India, 2nd T20I, October 31, 2025, 19:15 hrs Local Time, 19:15 hrs AEDT, 13:45 hrs IST

Where: MCG, Melbourne

What to expect: After a no result game in Canberra, signs aren't the brightest in Melbourne two days later. Ironically the Victorian capital has had flawless weather over the last two days but there's already been rain in the air on Friday morning with the clouds casting a very sombre look up in the skies. Most of the radars show the rains relenting post 5 pm, which could possibly allow for the match starting on time. Like in the last few summers, there'll be intrigue around how the pitch plays at the MCG, not just for the 40 overs here but for what it could mean for the rest of the season.

Team News

Australia

Though there were some expensive overs in between rain breaks for most of the Aussie bowlers on show, there is unlikely to be any changes made from the XI that fronted up in Canberra with Josh Philippe to continue as a specialist batter.

Probable XI:Travis Head, Mitchell Marsh (c), Josh Inglis (wk), Marcus Stoinis, Tim David, Mitch Owen, Josh Philippe, Nathan Ellis, Xavier Bartlett, Matthew Kuhnemann, Josh Hazlewood

India

Not for the first time, there will be eyebrows raised over the exclusion of Arshdeep Singh, India's most successful bowler in this format, in favour of Harshit Rana who adds some batting muscle to the lower-order. But India too will in all likelihood stick to the same combination from Wednesday night.

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav (c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson (wk), Shivam Dube, Axar Patel, Harshit Rana, Kuldeep Yadav, Varun Chakravarthy, Jasprit Bumrah

Squads:
Australia Squad: Mitchell Marsh(c), Travis Head, Josh Inglis(w), Tim David, Mitchell Owen, Marcus Stoinis, Josh Philippe, Xavier Bartlett, Nathan Ellis, Matthew Kuhnemann, Josh Hazlewood, Sean Abbott, Matthew Short, Ben Dwarshuis, Tanveer Sangha

snippet.title: One Direction - Night Changes (Lyrics)
snippet.description:
One Direction - Night Changes
Stream/Download:

(Lyrics):
[Verse 1: Zayn & Liam]
Goin' out tonight, changes into somethin' red
Her mother doesn't like that kind of dress
Everything she never had, she's showin' off
Drivin' too fast, moon is breakin' through her hair
She's headin' for somethin' that she won't forget
Havin' no regrets is all that she really wants

[Chorus: All & Harry]
(Ooh) We're only gettin' older, baby
(Ooh) And I've been thinkin' about it lately
(Ooh) Does it ever drive you crazy
(Ah-ah-ah) Just how fast the night changes?
(Ooh) Everything that you've ever dreamed of
(Ooh) Disappearin' when you wake up
(Ooh) But there's nothin' to be afraid of
(Ah-ah-ah) Even when the night changes
(Ooh) It will never change me and you

[Verse 2: Louis & Niall]
Chasin' her tonight, doubts are runnin' round her head
He's waitin', hides behind a cigarette

snippet.title: Arasan - Official Trailer | Dhanush | Silambarasan TR | Vetri Maaran | Anirudh Ravichander
snippet.description:
Arasan - Official Trailer | Dhanush | Silambarasan TR | Vetri Maaran | Anirudh Ravichander 

This video is made only for showcasing the editing skills of the individual

Arasan is the title of Tamil star Silambarasan TRâ€™s upcoming project with ace filmmaker Vetri Maaran, the makers announced on Tuesday (October 7). Produced by Kalaippuli S Thanu under his V Creations banner, the upcoming film is set in the world of Vetriâ€™s acclaimed 2018 film Vada Chennai.

                    Other details, like the plot, remain unknown. While announcing the film in June, director Vetri Maaran revealed that the film, then tentatively called STR 49, is a parallel narrative set around the same time as Vada Chennai, and that â€œcharacters and aspects from Vada Chennai will find their way into this story.
      
               A previously released promo video of the film showed a sickle-wielding Simbu, in a striped shirt and baggy pants, walking into a desolate lane. The video, however, cuts before his face is revealed. Interestingly, the title poster also intentionally hides the actorâ€™s face, which certainly adds to the mystery.

While cast details have yet to be officially revealed, a leaked still from the set showed director Nelson alongside Simbu, prompting netizens to speculate that the director is playing a cameo in the film. Further speculations added that actors Kavin and Manikandan are also part of the film, and that actors Andrea Jeremiah, Samuthirakani and Kishore are reprising their roles from Vada Chennai. Vada Chennai, widely considered as one of the best gangster dramas in Tamil, featured Dhanush as a young man who is pulled into a world of crime, one where you either do or die. Over the years, the film has attained cult status among audiences. Interestingly, Vetri had also announced a spin-off series centred around Ameer Sultanâ€™s character Rajan, titled Rajan Vagaiyara; however, there havenâ€™t been any updates on the same.

                    Other details, like the plot, remain unknown. While announcing the film in June, director Vetri Maaran revealed that the film, then tentatively called STR 49, is a parallel narrative set around the same time as Vada Chennai, and that â€œcharacters and aspects from Vada Chennai will find their way into this story.
      
               A previously released promo video of the film showed a sickle-wielding Simbu, in a striped shirt and baggy pants, walking into a desolate lane. The video, however, cuts before his face is revealed. Interestingly, the title poster also intentionally hides the actorâ€™s face, which certainly adds to the mystery.

While cast details have yet to be officially revealed, a leaked still from the set showed director Nelson alongside Simbu, prompting netizens to speculate that the director is playing a cameo in the film. Further speculations added that actors Kavin and Manikandan are also part of the film, and that actors Andrea Jeremiah, Samuthirakani and Kishore are reprising their roles from Vada Chennai. Vada Chennai, widely considered as one of the best gangster dramas in Tamil, featured Dhanush as a young man who is pulled into a world of crime, one where you either do or die. Over the years, the film has attained cult status among audiences. Interestingly, Vetri had also announced a spin-off series centred around Ameer Sultanâ€™s character Rajan, titled Rajan Vagaiyara; however, there havenâ€™t been any updates on the same.

snippet.title: Baahubali - The Epic Release Trailer (Telugu) | Prabhas, Rana | SS Rajamouli | 31st October 2025
snippet.description:
#BaahubaliTheEpic is a combined narrative of the two-part Indian film saga, weaving together the grandeur and drama of Baahubali: The Beginning and Baahubali: The Conclusion into one epic tale.

Worldwide Releasing On Oct 31st 2025.

CAST

Prabhas as Sivudu & Baahubali, Rana Daggubati as Bhallaladeva, Anushka Shetty as Devasena, Tamannaah as Avanthika with Ramya Krishna, Nasser, Sathyaraj, Kiccha Sudeepa, Adivi Sesh, Rakesh Varre, Meka Ramakrishna.

CREW

Screenplay & Direction: S.S. Rajamouli
Presented by: K. Raghavendra Rao B.A.
Producers: Shobu Yarlagadda & Prasad Devineni
Story: V. Vijayendra Prasad 
DOP: K.K. Senthil Kumar
Production Designer: Sabu Cyril
Music Composer: M.M. Keeravaani
VFX Supervision: V. Srinivas Mohan

snippet.title: Barati - Ajay Hooda | Pooja Hooda | Pardeep , Peehu | New Haryanvi Song 2025 | T-Series Haryanvi
snippet.description:
Presenting latest Haryanvi video song 2025 "Barati" sung by Harjeet Deewana, Komal Choudhary, Feat. Ajay Hooda. The music is given by Gulshan Music, while lyrics are penned by Ajay Hooda. Enjoy and stay connected with us !!

Song: Barati
Feat. Ajay Hooda.,Pooja Hooda, Pardeep Boora, Peehu Yadav, Miss Kannyy, Neenu Sindhar
Singer: Harjeet Deewana , Komal Chaudhary
Music: Gulshan Music
Lyrics: Ajay Hooda
Video: Kaka Films
Project: Naresh Kaka
Dop: Shelly Dhiman
Choreographer: Bunty one tak
Edit: Pawan Kumar
Makeup: Karan,  Raj
Hair:  Annu Maurya, Manisha taank
Dance Group: Karishma & Jassi 
Arts: KF & Team
Costume: Sneha Saini
Lights: Shiva Cine Light
Camera Lens : Saya Films
Bts: Sunny Rana
Catering : Ashok Kumar
Location Kachi Haveli Fbd.
Sp.Thanx Sanjay Swami 
Casting Crew.. Bansi 
Spot boys  :  Sagar , Ajay & Team     
Sound.. Mithun
Music Label: T Series
